cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely because the paper discusses the applicability of stream constraint programming to real-world planning and control problems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper introduces a new construct and a syntactic sugar for stream constraint programming. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper introduces a new construct adapted from Linear Temporal Logic and proposes novel solving algorithms for it. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible because the paper proposes new solving algorithms for the introduced constructs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible because the paper presents experimental results comparing the proposed approach with an existing method for verifying eventuality conditions using a CP approach.
